# Goals

---

## ApiSources-G1 API Source Configuration supports multi-provider LLM management with auto-detection and model tiers
**Status:** proposed
**Tags:** stack:backend
**Depends on:** AgentConfig-G1, Runtime-G3

- [ ] ApiSource data model supports Anthropic, OpenAI, and Local providers with per-source models
- [ ] ModelTier enum (Light / Mid / Heavy) maps to concrete models per provider
- [ ] First-startup auto-detection finds existing Claude keys, OpenAI keys, and Ollama instances
- [ ] API sources persisted to `dirs::data_local_dir()/autoforge/api_sources.json`
- [ ] CRUD API endpoints for creating, reading, updating, and deleting API sources
- [ ] Multi-provider AI dispatch routes chat requests to the correct provider (Anthropic SSE, OpenAI streaming, Local/Ollama)
- [ ] API key resolution priority: env var → ~/.claude/settings.json → stored (base64)
- [ ] Test Connection endpoint verifies API source connectivity and credentials
- [ ] APIs top-level view with source list, detail editor, and model management table
- [ ] First-startup UI guides user when no API source is configured

Currently AutoForge only supports Anthropic Claude with a hardcoded API key path. ApiSources-G1 introduces a configurable multi-provider system so agents can use different LLM backends. The APIs view sits as a top-level navigation tab alongside Chat, Specs, and Relay, because Tools and Skills views will follow the same pattern in the future.
---

## ApiSources-G2 APIs Documentation View
**Status:** implemented
**Tags:** stack:frontend
**Depends on:** ApiSources-G1

- [x] Top-level "APIs" tab in nav rail for browsing backend endpoint documentation
- [x] Lists all API routes grouped by module (project, chats, wiki, relay, config)
- [x] Displays method, path, handler name, and brief description per endpoint
- [x] Static content sourced from `specs/apis.ad`; editable via Specs workspace
